Package: TEHTree
Type: Package
Title: Treatment effect heterogeneity using conditional inference trees
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Julian Wolfson, Brandon Koch, Ashwini Venkatasubramaniam, David Vock and Lauren Erickson.
Maintainer: Ashwini Venkatasubramaniam <ashwinikv01@gmail.com>
Description: A novel approach to assessing effect heterogeneity of a randomised binary treatment. This method combines prognostic score matching and conditional inference trees to characterise the heterogeneity. Additionally, this method allows for the Type I error (i.e., the false discovery of subgroups) to be explicitly controlled.  
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
